comments: The most difficult, challenging course thus far in my graduate career; it really tested my limits. Emily is a great professor, but expects a lot from her class, so expect a heavy workload, but you will be rewarded with good grades if you meet her expectations.

She is too smart for BSC< she should be teaching at Harvard. However, she does not treat you like you are a HArvard student. SHe is fair, and expects alot from you. Two exams one panel. Her exams are unclear and tough, i got a 70 on the first and raised my second to a 85. the panel is easy as long as you have evidence to back your case. overall, sh
